      <unit unitid="SubSec_DirectionAngles" standalone="false">
         <titles>
            <title>Definition of Direction Angles</title>
            <plain.title>Definition</plain.title>
         </titles>
         <body>
            <block>
               <block.body>
                  <def type="Definition" id="Def_DirectionAngle">
                     <def.body>
                        <para>
                           <para.body>Given a vector <math>
                                 <latex>\mathbf{x}</latex>
                              </math> in <math>
                                 <latex>\RNr[n]</latex>
                              </math>, and a number <math>
                                 <latex>i</latex>
                              </math>, <math>
                                 <latex>1 \leq i \leq n</latex>
                              </math>, the <math>
                                 <latex>i</latex>
                              </math>-th direction angle of <math>
                                 <latex>\mathbf{x}</latex>
                              </math> is
					</para.body>
                           <index.glossary>
                              <term>direction angle</term>
                              <info>
                                 <info.caption>Direction Angle</info.caption>
                                 <para>
                                    <para.body>the angle between a given vector <math>
                                          <latex>\mathbf{x}</latex>
                                       </math> in <math>
                                          <latex>\RNr[n]</latex>
                                       </math> and one of the coordinate axes.</para.body>
                                 </para>
                              </info>
                           </index.glossary>
                        </para>
                        <para align="center">
                           <para.body>
                              <subordinate>
                                 <hot>
                                    <math>
                                       <latex>\omega_i\ :=\ \sphericalangle(\mathbf{e}_i,\mathbf{x})</latex>
                                    </math>
                                 </hot>
                                 <info>
                                    <info.caption>Read this as ...</info.caption>
                                    <para>
                                       <para.body>â€˜omega i is defined to be the angle from <math>
                                             <latex>\mathbf{e}_i</latex>
                                          </math> and <math>
                                             <latex>\mathbf{x}</latex>
                                          </math>.</para.body>
                                    </para>
                                 </info>
                              </subordinate>
                           </para.body>
                        </para>
                     </def.body>
                  </def>
                  <para>
                     <para.body>To compute direction angles we use the 
				<subordinate>
                           <hot>dot product</hot>
                           <info>
                              <info.caption>What does the Dot Product have to do with Direction Angles?</info.caption>
                              <para>
                                 <para.body>Indeed, if <math>
                                       <latex>\mathbf{x}</latex>
                                    </math> and <math>
                                       <latex>\mathbf{y}</latex>
                                    </math> are nonzero vectors, we know that</para.body>
                              </para>
                              <math.display>
                                 <latex>\mathbf{x} \bullet \mathbf{y} = | \mathbf{x} | | \mathbf{y} |\ \cos \sphericalangle( \mathbf{x} , \mathbf{y} )</latex>
                              </math.display>
                           </info>
                        </subordinate>, as in proposition below.</para.body>
                  </para>
                  <xi:include xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude"
                              href="DirectionAngleCompute_Prop.xml"/>
               </block.body>
            </block>
         </body>
